acceptance_criteria: "- npm run release:check passes after final changelog generation.\\n- Clean temporary project verifies local package install and changelog generation.\\n- pm validate has no file-link warnings for source files after governance links are updated.\\n- GitHub repository and release v0.1.0 are verified with gh.\\n- npm registry auth and package visibility are checked and the publication blocker is updated if auth is still unavailable.\\n- All intentional changes are committed and pushed, or the remaining external blocker is documented."
reviewer: steve
risk: medium
confidence: high
sprint: 2026-05-release
release: 0.1.0
resolution: "Final verification passed for release gates, strict pm validation, GitHub release metadata, and clean temp-folder local package install. npm publication remains externally blocked because this shell has no npm registry authentication and no npm token environment variables."
expected_result: All local and GitHub-controlled release checks pass; npm publication completes only when valid npm registry credentials are configured.
actual_result: "npm run release:check passed; pm validate returned ok=true with zero warnings; clean temp project /tmp/pm-changelog-final-AMwXqp installed the local package and generated a changelog containing the smoke item; gh release v0.1.0 is public and non-draft; npm publish --access public failed with ENEEDAUTH."
